  <b>Description</b>
  <blockquote>
    Quiet, upper 2 bedroom, 1 1/2 bathroom Villa St. Croix condo with very large south facing deck.
<br>
<br>AMENITIES INCLUDE:
<br>* Open floor plan featuring spacious living room with  new LVP flooring, vaulted ceilings, upgraded fireplace w/ mantle, recessed lighting, ceiling fan and sliding glass doors to expansive deck. 
<br>* Super functional kitchen with abundant pantry storage, granite counter tops, a breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances (dishwasher, gas stove, microwave, refrigerator (included as-is) and stacked washer &amp; dryer (also as-is).
<br>* Separate dining area off living room/kitchen with chandelier.  
<br>* Large master suite features wood laminate flooring, vaulted ceiling and a spacious walk-in closet. Attached bathroom has been upgraded with a newer vanity, countertops and a bathtub/shower combo.
<br>* Slate stairwell leads to second loft bedroom has attached half bath (sink and toilet).  Could be used as home office, craft room, etc.  
<br>* Huge corner deck off living room and master is perfect for entertaining, BBQs, dining outdoors and quiet relaxing.
<br>* Inside washer and dryer hookups (stacked washer &amp; dryer included AS-IS)
<br>* Single covered carport and abundant open/guest parking within the community. Community also has long term storage option for RVs, campers, etc. for additional fees.
<br>* Biking distance from world famous beaches and HB pier, dining, entertainment and shopping (Pacific City and Main Street are only a few blocks away).
<br>* Close to award winning schools and major freeways.
<br>* Gate guarded community with pool, spa, BBQs and a clubhouse.
<br>* Best location in complex.
<br>
<br>OTHER DETAILS:
<br>Available? Available immediately.
<br>Lease term? Minimum of one year lease required
<br>Pets? Subject to HOA and owner breed restrictions, dog may be considered with exceptional financials &amp; credit, increased deposit AND a $50/monthly pet rent.
<br>Smoking or vaping? Sorry, not permitted.
<br>Utilities? Tenant is responsible for electricity and gas. Water and trash provided by HOA.
<br>Other Services? Gardening provided by homeowners association.
<br>
<br>LEASING REQUIREMENTS:
<br>1) All adults (18 or older) who will reside in the home must submit an online application with copy of their ID and proof of income (if any).
<br>2) Gross combined household income should be a minimum of 3x the rent.
<br>3) We will run a credit report and we require good credit.
